==Old English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/weorθ/}}

===Etymology 1===
From Germanic ''*werþaz'' ‘towards, opposite’, used substantively as a noun.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[werth]], Old Saxon [[werþ]], Old High German [[werd]] (Dutch [[waard]] ''adj'', German [[wert]] ''adj'' [[Wert]] ''noun''), Old Norse [[verðr]] ''adj'' [[verð]] ''n'' (Swedish [[värd]]), Gothic [[𐍅𐌰𐌹𐍂𐌸𐍃]].

===Adjective===
'''weorþ'''
# [[worth]], [[deserving]]
# [[honoured]], [[esteemed]]

===Noun===
'''weorþ''' ''n'' (plural same)
# [[worth]], [[price]], [[value]]
# [[honour]], [[dignity]]

